 incorporating these conceptual frameworks into disciplinary language instruction and follows four focal participants as they learn to read and write new genres in a second language and disciplinary culture. By examining not just students’ written texts, but also their reading practices and interactions in class and in tutoring sessions, the book traces the ways in which disciplinary knowledge and language interact as students develop academic literacy in a new disciplinary community. Throughout the book, the discipline of law is used as a lens for examining broader connections between language, culture and disciplinary knowledge, and their relevance for English for Specific Purposes and writing in the disciplines.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teaching. 0aLawxLanguagexStudy and teaching. 0aLawxMethodologyxStudy and teaching. 0aLegal compositionxStudy and teaching. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / English as a Second Language.2bisacsh  aAcademic literacy.  aELP.  aESP.  aEnglish for Legal Purposes.  aEnglish for Specific Purposes.  aclassroom-based research.  adisciplinary specificity.  alegal writing.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066312908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060670640uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978178309851440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781783098514423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781783098514/original  a978-3-11-060670-6  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066312-9  MultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  